"adj. 同词源的；同类的 【英】 adj. 同词源的 (related through the same source)；同类的 (having the same nature or quality) 【记】 cogn(认识)+ate→认 识的→同类的 【同】 同根词：cognizance( 认识，观察); recognize(认出) adj. 同词源的(来自相同的词根); 有血缘关系的; 有共同祖先的 【例】Physics and philosophy are cognate sciences 物理与哲学是同源科学. 【记】cogn认识, ate吃－认识到吃的重要性－因为我们是同类的co共同, gn, ate吃: 同类才一起吃饭呢? 我想你们不会和dog一起吃吧! 【参】cognizance(n 认识, 观察); recognize(v 认出) 【记】co + native 同一个native，g可省略； cog + native同宗都认识 cognate (adj.)  1640s, from Latin cognatus ""of common descent,"" from com- ""together"" (see co-) + gnatus, past participle of gnasci, older form of nasci ""to be born"" (see genus). Words that are cognates are cousins, not siblings. As a noun, from 1754."
